## Rules

- A: use lowercase for type and scope
- A: use imperative mood in subject
- N: end subject with period
- A: explain non-obvious changes in body
- A: reference related issues in footer
- A: commit by logical units - group related changes together (e.g., all husky hooks, all docs, all configs)
- A: amend commits when making follow-up fixes to the same change (typos, lint errors, formatting)
- Version bumping is automatic: feat = minor, fix/perf/refactor = patch, BREAKING CHANGE = major
- Changelog generation is automatic
